nby\n| score = 8\u20132\n| report =<ref name=\"roopes_rooster\">{{cite news\n| title =Roope\u2019s Rooster/Ponsonby V North Shore/Newton Defeats Otahuhu\n| page =8\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16295\n| date = 1916-07-31\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160731.2.77.1| accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>\n| away = North Shore\n| try1 = L Martin 2\n| con1 = J Winters\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Jack Paul (one mark)\n| stadium = Victoria 1\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Murray\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 29 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 22\u20138\n| report =<ref name=\"roopes_rooster\" />\n| away = Otahuhu\n| try1 = [[George Iles]] 2, Thomas 2, Joe Bennett, R Lovett\n| con1 = Coates, Potier\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Spinley, Stanaway\n| con2 = Stanaway\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 2\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Whitley\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 29 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = WBD-LBD\n| report =<ref name=\"roopes_rooster\" />| away = Grafton\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 3\n| attendance =\n| referee = Fielding\n}}\n\n===Semi-finals===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 5 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 5\u20135\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Roope\u2019s Rooster/City V Ponsonby\n| page =8\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16301\n| date = 1916-08-07\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160807.2.118.1| accessdate = 2019-08-14}}</ref>| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = J Sutton\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = [[Thomas McClymont]]\n| con2 = A Cross\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Herrick\n}}\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 12 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 16\u20133\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Roope Rooster Match/City Defeats Newton\n| page =8\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16037\n| date = 1916-08-14\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160814.2.94.1| accessdate = 2019-08-14}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], [[Jim Rukutai]], Harry Francis, J Sutton\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 =\n| drop1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = Arthur Isles\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n===Final===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 19 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 11\u20135\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Roope Rooster Competition/Won by City Rovers/City Defeats Ponsonby\n| page =3\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16313\n| date = 1916-09-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160821.2.5.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-13}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = R Clarke, [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], H Lunn\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = [[Thomas McClymont]]\n| con2 = A Cross\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = T Fielding\n}}\n\n==Top point and try scorers==\nThe following point scoring lists include both Senior Championship matches and the Roope Rooster competition. [[Karl Ifwersen]] was the top point scorer for the third consecutive year with 58 points. He also topped the try scoring list with 8.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries\n|-\n|1||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||Grafton Athletic||8\n|-\n|2||Nicholson||North Shore||7\n|-\n|2||[[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]||North Shore||7\n|-\n|2||[[George Iles]]||Newton Rangers||7\n|-\n|5||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||5\n|-\n|5||Perrett||North Shore||5\n|-\n|7||T Paul||North Shore||4\n|-\n|7||J Sutton||City Rovers||4\n|-\n|7||[[Jim Rukutai]]||City Rovers||4\n|-\n|7||[[Thomas McClymont]]||Ponsonby United||4\n|-\n|7||L Martin||Ponsonby United||4\n|-\n|7||D Norgrove||Ponsonby United||4\n|-\n|7||[[Dougie McGregor]]||Grafton Athletic||4\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Rank!!Player!!Team!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!DG!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||Grafton Athletic||8||6||10||0||0||56\n|-\n|2||Jack Paul||North Shore||1||14||7||2||0||49\n|-\n|3||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||5||2||3||1||2||31\n|-\n|4||[[George Iles]]||Newton Rangers||7||1||0||0||0||23\n|-\n|5||[[Ernie Asher]]||City Rovers||0||6||5||0||0||22\n|-\n|6||Nicholson||North Shore||7||0||0||0||0||21\n|-\n|6||[[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]||North Shore||7||0||0||0||0||21\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Lower grade clubs==\nThe Telegraph Messengers Club nominated a team for the Sixth Grade. They were usually named Post and Telegraph in the media reports during the season.\n*[[Manukau Magpies|Manukau]]\n*[[Northcote Tigers|Northcote Ramblers]]\n*[[Post and Telegraph]]\n*[[Richmond Rovers|Richmond]]\n*Riverhead\n*Sunnyside\n*[[Thames Old Boys]]\n\n==End of season exhibition matches==\nThe week after the final was played [[City Rovers]] travelled to [[Ngaruawahia]] to play Lower Waikato. City won by 13 points to 9. A week later [[Richmond Rovers|Richmond]] and Thames Old Boys (based in Auckland) traveled to [[Thames]] to play a match. It was won by Thames Old Boys by 11 to 5.<ref>{{cite news \n| title = Excursion to Thames/Richmond V Old Boys\n| page =8\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16325\n| date = 1916-09-04\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160904.2.115.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-13}}</ref>\n\nThe last match of the season was played on 9 September when [[City Rovers]] played against Lower Waikato at [[Victoria Park, Auckland|Victoria Park]]. [[City Rovers]] won by 19 points to 8. This brought the [[Auckland Rugby League]] season to a close. The curtain-raiser was a match between the Referees Association and Auckland rugby league players and was won by the referees by 10 points to 5.<ref>{{cite news \n| title = Waikato v City Rovers/The Season Closed\n| page =10\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=LIII |issue=16331\n| date = 1916-09-11\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19160911.2.117.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-14}}</ref>\n\n==Representative fixtures==\nThere were no representative fixtures played in 1916 owing to the effects of the war on senior playing numbers.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:1916 in New Zealand rugby league|Auckland Rugby League]]\n", "name_user": "Can I Log In", "label": "safe", "comment": "Everything about this article is wrong in someway", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1916_Auckland_Rugby_League_season"}
{"title_page": "Andrej Panadi\u0107", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Andrej Panadi\u0107\n| image = Andrej Panadi\u0107.jpg\n| caption = Panadi\u0107 with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]]\n| fullname = Andrej Panadi\u0107\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1969|3|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Zagreb]], SFR Yugoslavia\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = 1.88m\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| clubnumber = \n| currentclub = \n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Radnik Velika Gorica]]\n| years1 = 1988\u20131994\n| clubs1 = [[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]\n| caps1  = 148\n| goals1 = 14\n| years2 = 1994\u20131996\n| clubs2 = [[Chemnitzer FC]]\n| caps2  = 65\n| goals2 = 6\n| years3 = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs3 = [[KFC Uerdingen 05]]\n| caps3  = 45\n| goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 1997\u20132001\n| clubs4 = [[Hamburger SV]]\n| caps4  = 101\n| goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2002\n| clubs5 = [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]]\n| caps5  = 14\n| goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2002\u20132004\n| clubs6 = [[Nagoya Grampus|Nagoya Grampus Eight]]\n| caps6  = 51\n| goals6 = 3\n| totalcaps = 410\n| totalgoals = 30\n| nationalyears1 = 1989\u20131990\n| nationalteam1  = [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2007\u20132008\n| managerclubs1 = [[NK Radnik Velika Gorica|Radnik]]\n| manageryears2 = 2008\n| managerclubs2 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| manageryears3 = 2016\n| managerclubs3 = [[NK Istra 1961|Istra 1961]]\n| manageryears4 = 2019\n| managerclubs4 = [[NK Kr\u0161ko|Kr\u0161ko]]\n| manageryears5 = 2019\u20132020\n| managerclubs5 = [[NK Rudar Velenje|Rudar Velenje]]\n|medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCompetition|Representing {{fb|YUG}}}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|UEFA U-21 Euro]]|[[1990 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|1990]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Andrej Panadi\u0107''' (born 9 March 1969) is a Croatian [[coach (sport)|football manager]] and a former [[Defender (association football)|defender]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/andrej-panadic/ | title = Andrej Panadi\u0107 | publisher = worldfootball.net | accessdate = 27 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe played for [[Dinamo Zagreb]] (1988\u20131994), [[Chemnitzer FC]] (1994\u20131996), [[KFC Uerdingen 05]] (1996), [[Hamburger SV]] (1997\u20132002), [[Sturm Graz]] (2001\u20132002), and [[Nagoya Grampus|Nagoya Grampus Eight]] (2002\u20132004).\n\nWith Dinamo Zagreb he won a Croatian championship in 1993.\n\nHe played for the [[Yugoslavia national football team]] and was a participant at the [[1990 FIFA World Cup]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n<ref name=\"national\">{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/18392/Andrej_Panadic.html|title=Andrej Panadi\u0107|publisher=www.national-football-teams.com|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n|-\n! Season\n! Club\n! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 |Yugoslavia\n! colspan=2 | League\n|-\n|1988\u201389||rowspan=\"3\"|[[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]||rowspan=\"3\"|[[Yugoslav First League|First League]]||28||3\n|-\n|1989\u201390||30||4\n|-\n|1990\u201391||18||0\n|-\n! colspan=3 |Croatia\n! colspan=2 | League\n|-\n|1992||[[NK Dinamo Zagreb|HA\u0160K-Gra\u0111anski]]||rowspan=\"3\"|[[Prva HNL]]||20||0\n|-\n|1992\u201393||rowspan=\"2\"|[[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Croatia Zagreb]]||29||3\n|-\n|1993\u201394||23||4\n|-\n! colspan=3 |Germany\n! colspan=2 | League\n|-\n|1994\u201395||rowspan=\"2\"|[[Chemnitzer FC]]||rowspan=\"4\"|[[2. Bundesliga]]||32||4\n|-\n|1995\u201396||33||2\n|-\n|1996\u201397||rowspan=\"2\"|[[KFC Uerdingen 05]]||31||2\n|-\n|1997\u201398||14||1\n|-\n|1997\u201398||rowspan=\"5\"|[[Hamburger SV]]||rowspan=\"5\"|[[Bundesliga]]||13||2\n|-\n|1998\u201399||26||2\n|-\n|1999\u201300||29||1\n|-\n|2000\u201301||24